  "reasoning": "Concatenate decimal representations of 10 and 2019 to get w = 102019. The sum of digits S(w) = 1+0+2+0+1+9 = 13, so k = S(w) - 10 = 3. Given a = 1 + x/y and b = 1 + y/x with x, y > 0 and a^2 + b^2 = 15. From (a-1)(b-1) = (x/y)*(y/x) = 1, we get ab - (a+b) = 0, so ab = a+b. Let s = a+b, then ab = s, and a^2 + b^2 = s^2 - 2s = 15, yielding s^2 - 2s - 15 = 0, so s = 5 (since s > 0). Then a^3 + b^3 = (a+b)(a^2 + b^2 - ab) = 5*(15-5) = 50.",
